Series:
  Enheduanna (2300 BCE) — 4 volumes
  Ada Lovelace (1843) — 4 volumes
  Faraday (1836) — 4 volumes
  The Workbench — 8 pamphlets + 1 field manual

Total volumes: 21

Subjects:
  Enheduanna — world's first named author, High Priestess of Ur, ~2300 BCE
  Ada Lovelace — mathematician, author of the first algorithm, 1843
  Michael Faraday — physicist, inventor of the Faraday cage, 1836
  The Workbench — electronics making tradition (ongoing)

All HTML files self-contained. Only Google Fonts as external dependency.
Pure browser-side — no build step, no framework, no server required.
